  "question": "How does the procedure end?",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The royal decree granting the name change must be published in the Belgian Official Gazette to inform the public. The name change becomes final on this date. In exceptional and duly proven circumstances, an exemption from publication may be requested. The opinion of the public prosecutor is sought during the procedure regarding this exemption."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The FPS Justice forwards the royal decree to the Civil Status Records Database (BAEC) within 15 days, and a note is added to documents linked to the individual concerned."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If there are no Belgian civil status records, the civil registrar of the place of residence will draw up a name change act in the BAEC."
    },
